                 "genf.mu.int", "genf.mu.ref", "genf.sigma.int", "genf.sigma.ref", "genf.Q.int", "genf.Q.ref", "genf.P.int", "genf.P.ref", "genf.mu.TE")

                    		
                  

                  

                    313
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    314
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    315
                    !
                    
                      
  col_names_final <- col_names[col_names %in%  names(params_all) ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    316
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    317
                    !
                    
                      
  params_all <- params_all %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    318
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::select(col_names_final)

                    		
                  

                  

                    319
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    320
                    
                    
                      
  # as a vector version with just numerics - needed for bootstrapping

                    		
                  

                  

                    321
                    !
                    
                      
  paramV <- as.numeric(params_all)

                    		
                  

                  

                    322
                    !
                    
                      
  names(paramV) <- paste0("comshp.", colnames(params_all))

                    		
                  

                  

                    323
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    324
                    
                    
                      
  #######################################################

                    		
                  

                  

                    325
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    326
                    
                    
                      
  #collect and return output

                    		
                  

                  

                    327
                    !
                    
                      
  output <- list(

                    		
                  

                  

                    328
                    !
                    
                      
    models = models.out,

                    		
                  

                  

                    329
                    !
                    
                      
    model_summary = model_summary.out,

                    		
                  

                  

                    330
                    !
                    
                      
    parameters_vector = paramV

                    		
                  

                  

                    331
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    332
                    !
                    
                      
  return(output)

                    		
                  

                  

                    333
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                
              

            

            

              

                
                  

                    1
                    
                    
                      
# NOT EXPORTED - called by runPSM

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
# Run a complete parametric survival analysis for one-arm

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
# Fits a single \code{\link{flexsurv}} models using \code{\link{flexsurvreg}}.

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
# @param data A data frame containing individual patient data for the relevant

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#   time to event outcomes. This is passed to the \code{data} argument of the

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#   \code{\link{fit_models}} function

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
# @param time_var Name of time variable in 'data'. Variable must be numerical and >0.

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
# @param  event_var Name of event variable in 'data'. Variable must be

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#   numerical and contain 1's to indicate an event and 0 to indicate a censor.

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
# @param  weight_var Optional name of a variable in "data" containing case weights.

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
# @param int_name Character to indicate the name of the treatment of interest,

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#   must be a level of the "strata_var" column in "data", used for labeling

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#   the parameters.

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
# @param distr A vector string of distributions, see dist argument in

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#   \code{\link{flexsurvreg}}. This is passed to the \code{distr} argument of

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#   the \code{\link{fit_models}} function. Default is all available distributions (see below).

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
# @details Possible distributions include:

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
# \itemize{

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#   \item Exponential ('exp')

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#   \item Weibull ('weibull')

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#   \item Gompertz ('gompertz')

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#   \item Log-normal ('lnorm')

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#   \item Log-logistic ('llogis')

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#   \item Generalized gamma ('gengamma')

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#   \item Gamma ('gamma')

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
#   \item Generalised F ('genf')

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
#   }

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
#

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
#   The model fit is in the form Surv(Time, Event==1) ~ 1 and is fit to the entire data (no strata). The parameters for each

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
#   treatment, are derived directly from the model (no additional manipulation

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
#   is required).

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
# @return A list containing 'models' (output from \code{\link{fit_models}}), 'model_summary' (output from\code{\link{get_model_summary}}) and

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
#   'parameters', a data frame containing the coefficients of each flexsurv model.

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
# \itemize{

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      
#   \item 'models' is a list of flexsurv objects for each distribution specified

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
#   \item 'model_summary' is a tibble object containing the fitted model objects, the parameter

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
#   estimates (\code{\link{coef}}),  \code{\link{AIC}} and \code{\link{BIC}}

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
#   from flexsurv objects.

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    
                    
                      
#   \item 'parameters' is a data frame with with one row which contains the coefficients for all of the flexsurv models specified.

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    
                    
                      
#    The column names are in the format 'distribution.parameter.TreatmentName', for example, weibull.shape.Intervention refers to the shape parameter

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
#     of the weibull distribution for the intervention treatment.}

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      
#

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    
                    
                      
# @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    46

                    1
                    
                    
                      
#' Extract information about fitted parametric survival models

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' @param x An object created by calling \code{\link{runPSM}}

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' @param types A list of statistics to extract - see \code{\link{summary.flexsurvreg}} for details

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' @param t The time points to be used - see \code{\link{summary.flexsurvreg}} for details

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' @param ci Should a confidence interval be returned - see \code{\link{summary.flexsurvreg}} for details

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' @param se Should a standard error be returned - see \code{\link{summary.flexsurvreg}} for details

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' 

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' @return A data frame containing the following values

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' \itemize{

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item Model - The Model as specified in \code{\link{runPSM}} model.type

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item ModelF - an ordered factor of Model

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item Dist - The distribution

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item DistF - an ordered factor of Dist

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item distr - as specified in \code{\link{runPSM}} distr

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item Strata - Either Intervention or Reference

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item StrataName - As specified by int_name and ref_name respectively in \code{\link{runPSM}}

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item type - as defined by the types parameter see \code{\link{summary.flexsurvreg}} for details

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item variable - "est", "lcl", "ucl", "se" respectively

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item time - either NA or the time the statistic is evaluated at

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item value - estimated value

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#'   }

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#'   

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#' 

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#' require(dplyr)

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
#' require(ggplot2)

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
#' 

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
#' PFS_data <- sim_adtte(seed = 2020, rho = 0.6) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
#' filter(PARAMCD=="PFS") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
#' transmute(USUBJID,

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
#'             ARMCD,

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
#'             PFS_days = AVAL,

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
#'             PFS_event = 1- CNSR

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
#' )

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      
#' 

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
#' psm_pfs <- runPSM(

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
#'   data = PFS_data,

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
#'   time_var = "PFS_days",

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    
                    
                      
#'   event_var = "PFS_event",

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    
                    
                      
#'   strata_var = "ARMCD",

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
#'   int_name = "A",

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      
#'   ref_name = "B")

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    
                    
                      
#' 

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
#' summaryPSM(psm_pfs, types = c("mean","rmst"), t = c(100,2000)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    
                    
                      
#'    filter(Dist == "Generalized Gamma", Strata == "Intervention")

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      
#' 

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    
                    
                      
#' summaryPSM(psm_pfs, types = "survival", t = seq(0,2000,100)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    
                    
                      
#'   ggplot(aes(x=time, y = value, color = StrataName, linetype = Model)) +

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    
                    
                      
#'   geom_line()+

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    
                    
                      
#'   facet_grid(~Dist)

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    
                    
                      
#' summaryPSM(psm_pfs, types = "hazard", t = seq(0,5000,100)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    
                    
                      
#'   ggplot(aes(x=time, y = value, color = StrataName, linetype = Model)) +

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    
                    
                      
#'   geom_line()+

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    
                    
                      
#'   facet_grid(~Dist) +

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    
                    
                      
#'   coord_cartesian(ylim = c(0,0.02))

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    
                    
                      
#' summaryPSM(psm_pfs, types = "cumhaz", t = seq(0,5000,100)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    
                    
                      
#'   ggplot(aes(x=time, y = value, color = StrataName, linetype = Model)) +

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    
                    
                      
#'   geom_line()+

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    
                    
                      
#'   facet_grid(~Dist) +

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    
                    
                      
#'   coord_cartesian(ylim = c(0,100))

                    		
                  

                  

                    65

                    66

                    67
                    
                    
                      
summaryPSM <- function(x,

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    
                    
                      
                          types = c("mean", "survival", "hazard", "cumhaz", "median", "rmst"),

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    
                    
                      
                          t = NULL,

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    
                    
                      
                          ci = FALSE,

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    
                    
                      
                          se = FALSE

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    
                    
                      
                          ){

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    
                    
                      
 

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    
                    
                      
  # check x is an object from runPSM

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    !
                    
                      
  assertthat::assert_that(

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    !
                    
                      
    any(names(x) == c("parameters_vector")) & any(names(x) == c("model_summary")),

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    !
                    
                      
    msg = "x must be created using runPSM"

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    
                    
                      
  # fix bindings check

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    !
                    
                      
  mdl1 <- mdl2 <- mdl3 <- ARM <- ARM2 <- NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    !
                    
                      
  model.type <- distr <-  Model <- Dist <- Strata <- type <- variable <- time <- value <- NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    
                    
                      
  # impute t if not provided

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    !
                    
                      
  if (is.null(t)){

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    !
                    
                      
    t <- seq(0, max(x$models[[1]]$data$Y[,"time"]), length.out = 10)

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    
                    
                      
  # extract metadata from the PSM model

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    !
                    
                      
  int_name <- x$model_summary$Intervention_name[1]

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    !
                    
                      
  if("Reference_name" %in% names(x$model_summary)){

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    !
                    
                      
    ref_name <- x$model_summary$Reference_name[1]

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    
                    
                      
  } else{

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    !
                    
                      
    ref_name <- NA

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    
                    
                      
  # distinguish between models with and without treatment effects

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    !
                    
                      
  noarm.models <- x$models[which(grepl("onearm." ,names(x$models)) |grepl("sep." ,names(x$models)))]

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    !
                    
                      
  arm.models <- x$models[which(grepl("shp." ,names(x$models)))]

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    
                    
                      
  # build appropriate new data for the models with and without parameters

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    !
                    
                      
  arm.newdata <- data.frame(ARM = c("Int", "Ref"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    104
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    105
                    !
                    
                      
  temp.df <- tibble::tibble(mdl = "", ARM = "", type = "", variable = "", time = 1, value = 1) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::filter(1 ==2)

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    
                    
                      
  ##################################################

                    		
                  

                  

                    109
                    
                    
                      
  # cycle through the types and extract information

                    		
                  

                  

                    110
                    
                    
                      
  ##################################################

                    		
                  

                  

                    111
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    112
                    !
                    
                      
  for (j in 1:length(types)){

                    		
                  

                  

                    113
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    114
                    !
                    
                      
    this.type <- types[j]

                    		
                  

                  

                    115
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    116
                    
                    
                      
    # for mean and median need to force t to be null 

                    		
                  

                  

                    117
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    118
                    !
                    
                      
    if(this.type %in% c("mean", "median")){

                    		
                  

                  

                    119
                    
                    
                      
      # cycle through the models

                    		
                  

                  

                    120
                    !
                    
                      
      lst1 <- lapply(noarm.models, FUN = tryFlexSurvPlusSummary, t = NULL, ci=ci, se=se, type = this.type) 

                    		
                  

                  

                    121
                    !
                    
                      
      lst2 <- lapply(arm.models, FUN = tryFlexSurvPlusSummary, t = NULL, ci=ci, se=se, type = this.type, newdata=arm.newdata)

                    		
                  

                  

                    122
                    
                    
                      
    } else{

                    		
                  

                  

                    123
                    
                    
                      
      # cycle through the models

                    		
                  

                  

                    124
                    !
                    
                      
      lst1 <- lapply(noarm.models, FUN = tryFlexSurvPlusSummary, t = t, ci=ci, se=se, type = this.type) 

                    		
                  

                  

                    125
                    !
                    
                      
      lst2 <- lapply(arm.models, FUN = tryFlexSurvPlusSummary, t = t, ci=ci, se=se, type = this.type, newdata=arm.newdata)

                    		
                  

                  

                    126
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    127
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    128
                    
                    
                      
    # combine and get the names of the models as define distributions etc

                    		
                  

                  

                    129
                    !
                    
                      
    this.lst <- c(lst1,lst2) 

                    		
                  

                  

                    130
                    !
                    
                      
    this.lbls <- names(this.lst)

                    		
                  

                  

                    131
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    132
                    !
                    
                      
    for (i in 1:length(this.lbls)){

                    		
                  

                  

                    133
                    !
                    
                      
      this.lst[[i]]$mdl = this.lbls[i]

                    		
                  

                  

                    134
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    135
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    136
                    !
                    
                      
    this.df <- dplyr::bind_rows(this.lst)

                    		
                  

                  

                    137
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    138
                    
                    
                      
    # append to other results

                    		
                  

                  

                    139
                    !
                    
                      
    temp.df <- temp.df %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    140
                    !
                    
                      
      dplyr::bind_rows(this.df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    141
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    142
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    143
                    
                    
                      
  ##################################################

                    		
                  

                  

                    144
                    
                    
                      
  # decode the model names

                    		
                  

                  

                    145
                    
                    
                      
  ##################################################

                    		
                  

                  

                    146
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    147
                    !
                    
                      
  s1 <- strsplit(temp.df$mdl, split = ".", fixed = TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    148
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    149
                    !
                    
                      
  final.df <- temp.df %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    150
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::mutate(

                    		
                  

                  

                    151
                    !
                    
                      
      mdl1 = sapply(s1, function(x){x[1]}),

                    		
                  

                  

                    152
                    !
                    
                      
      mdl2 = sapply(s1, function(x){x[2]}),

                    		
                  

                  

                    153
                    !
                    
                      
      mdl3 = sapply(s1, function(x){x[3]}),

                    		
                  

                  

                    154
                    !
                    
                      
      model.type = mdl1,

                    		
                  

                  

                    155
                    !
                    
                      
      distr = ifelse(mdl1 == "onearm", mdl3, mdl2),

                    		
                  

                  

                    156
                    !
                    
                      
      ARM2 = ifelse(mdl1 == "onearm", mdl2, mdl3),

                    		
                  

                  

                    157
                    
                    
                      
      # decodes

                    		
                  

                  

                    158
                    !
                    
                      
      Strata = ifelse(is.na(ARM2), 

                    		
                  

                  

                    159
                    !
                    
                      
                      ifelse(ARM=="Int", "Intervention", "Reference"),

                    		
                  

                  

                    160
                    !
                    
                      
                      ifelse(ARM2 == "int", "Intervention", "Reference")

                    		
                  

                  

                    161
                    
                    
                      
                      )

                    		
                  

                  

                    162
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    163
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    164
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    165
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    166
                    
                    
                      
  ####################################################################################

                    		
                  

                  

                    167
                    
                    
                      
  # Add factors for easy sort

                    		
                  

                  

                    168
                    
                    
                      
  ####################################################################################

                    		
                  

                  

                    169
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    170
                    
                    
                      
  # define factors for models

                    		
                  

                  

                    171
                    !
                    
                      
  Model.levels <- c("Kaplan Meier",

                    		
                  

                  

                    172
                    !
                    
                      
                    "Common shape", "Independent shape",

                    		
                  

                  

                    173
                    !
                    
                      
                    "Separate - Reference", "Separate - Intervention",

                    		
                  

                  

                    174
                    !
                    
                      
                    "One arm - Intervention")

                    		
                  

                  

                    175
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    176
                    !
                    
                      
  Dist.orig <- c("exp", "weibull", "lnorm", "gamma", "gengamma", 

                    		
                  

                  

                    177
                    !
                    
                      
                 "genf", "llogis", "gompertz", "Kaplan Meier")

                    		
                  

                  

                    178
                    !
                    
                      
  Dist.levels <- c("Exponential", "Weibull", "Log Normal", "Gamma", "Generalized Gamma", 

                    		
                  

                  

                    179
                    !
                    
                      
                   "Generalized F", "Log Logistic", "Gompertz", "Kaplan Meier")

                    		
                  

                  

                    180
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    181
                    !
                    
                      
  rc <- final.df %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    182
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::transmute(

                    		
                  

                  

                    183
                    !
                    
                      
      Model = ifelse(model.type == "indshp","Independent shape",

                    		
                  

                  

                    184
                    !
                    
                      
                     ifelse(model.type == "comshp", "Common shape", 

                    		
                  

                  

                    185
                    !
                    
                      
                            paste0(ifelse(model.type == "sep", "Separate", "One arm"), " - ", Strata))),

                    		
                  

                  

                    186
                    !
                    
                      
      ModelF = factor(Model, levels = Model.levels, ordered = TRUE),

                    		
                  

                  

                    187
                    !
                    
                      
      Dist = as.character(factor(distr, levels=Dist.orig, labels = Dist.levels)),

                    		
                  

                  

                    188
                    !
                    
                      
      DistF = factor(Dist, levels = Dist.levels, ordered = TRUE),

                    		
                  

                  

                    189
                    !
                    
                      
      distr,

                    		
                  

                  

                    190
                    !
                    
                      
      Strata,

                    		
                  

                  

                    191
                    !
                    
                      
      StrataName = ifelse(Strata == "Intervention", int_name, ref_name),

                    		
                  

                  

                    192
                    !
                    
                      
      type,

                    		
                  

                  

                    193
                    !
                    
                      
      variable,

                    		
                  

                  

                    194
                    !
                    
                      
      time,

                    		
                  

                  

                    195
                    !
                    
                      
      value) 

                    		
                  

                  

                    196
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    197
                    !
                    
                      
  return(rc)

                    		
                  

                  

                    198
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    199
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                  

                    200
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    201
                    
                    
                      
############################################################################################################

                    		
                  

                  

                    202
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    203
                    
                    
                      
# helper function that adds error handling to summary.flexsurvreg 

                    		
                  

                  

                    204
                    
                    
                      
# and standardises return format

                    		
                  

                  

                    205
                    
                    
                      
# just used internally

                    		
                  

                  

                    206
                    
                    
                      
# creates tidy data returns even if models do not converge to simplify later processing

                    		
                  

                  

                    207
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    208
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    209
                    
                    
                      
tryFlexSurvPlusSummary <- function(object, type, newdata = NULL, ci = TRUE, se = FALSE, t = NULL){

                    		
                  

                  

                    210
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    211
                    
                    
                      
  # fix bindings check

                    		
                  

                  

                    212
                    !
                    
                      
  est <- lcl <- ucl <- NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    213
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    214
                    
                    
                      
  # define a structure for return

                    		
                  

                  

                    215
                    !
                    
                      
  rc_struct <- tibble::tibble(

                    		
                  

                  

                    216
                    !
                    
                      
    ARM = "",

                    		
                  

                  

                    217
                    !
                    
                      
    type = "",

                    		
                  

                  

                    218
                    !
                    
                      
    variable = "",

                    		
                  

                  

                    219
                    !
                    
                      
    time = NaN,

                    		
                  

                  

                    220
                    !
                    
                      
    value = NaN) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    221
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::filter(1 == 2)

                    		
                  

                  

                    222
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    223
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    224
                    
                    
                      
  # check object is ok

                    		
                  

                  

                    225
                    !
                    
                      
  assertthat::assert_that(

                    		
                  

                  

                    226
                    !
                    
                      
    class(object) == "flexsurvreg",

                    		
                  

                  

                    227
                    !
                    
                      
    msg = "object must be flexsurvreg"

                    		
                  

                  

                    228
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    229
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    230
                    
                    
                      
  # check newdata matches expected format

                    		
                  

                  

                    231
                    !
                    
                      
  assertthat::assert_that(

                    		
                  

                  

                    232
                    !
                    
                      
    ifelse(is.null(newdata), TRUE, names(newdata) == "ARM"),

                    		
                  

                  

                    233
                    !
                    
                      
    msg = "Only models defined with flexsurvplus can be handled"

                    		
                  

                  

                    234
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    235
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    236
                    
                    
                      
  # try and get the summary

                    		
                  

                  

                    237
                    !
                    
                      
  rc.summ <- tryCatch(summary(object, type = type, newdata=newdata, t=t, ci = ci, se = se, tidy = TRUE), error = function(e) {e})

                    		
                  

                  

                    238
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    239
                    !
                    
                      
  stat_levels <- c("est", "lcl", "ucl", "se")[c(TRUE,ci,ci,se)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    240
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    241
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    242
                    
                    
                      
  # catch the error and return an empty data frame

                    		
                  

                  

                    243
                    !
                    
                      
  if ("error" %in% class(rc.summ)){

                    		
                  

                  

                    244
                    
                    
                      
    # check expected levels as a function of newdata and t

                    		
                  

                  

                    245
                    
                    
                      
    # build a data frame matching format

                    		
                  

                  

                    246
                    !
                    
                      
    ARM_levels = ifelse(is.null(newdata), NA, newdata$ARM)

                    		
                  

                  

                    247
                    !
                    
                      
    t_levels = ifelse(is.null(t), NA, t)

                    		
                  

                  

                    248
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    249
                    !
                    
                      
    rc <- expand.grid(ARM = ARM_levels, time = t_levels, variable = stat_levels) 

                    		
                  

                  

                    250
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    251
                    
                    
                      
    # no error so build a data frame of statistics 

                    		
                  

                  

                    252
                    
                    
                      
  } else{

                    		
                  

                  

                    253
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    254
                    
                    
                      
    # estimate

                    		
                  

                  

                    255
                    !
                    
                      
    rc <- rc.summ %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    256
                    !
                    
                      
      dplyr::transmute(variable = "est",

                    		
                  

                  

                    257
                    !
                    
                      
                value = est,

                    		
                  

                  

                    258
                    !
                    
                      
                ARM = "",

                    		
                  

                  

                    259
                    !
                    
                      
                time = NA) 

                    		
                  

                  

                    260
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    261
                    
                    
                      
    # cis requested

                    		
                  

                  

                    262
                    !
                    
                      
    if(ci){

                    		
                  

                  

                    263
                    !
                    
                      
      rc.lcl <- rc.summ %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    264
                    !
                    
                      
        dplyr::transmute(ARM = "",

                    		
                  

                  

                    265
                    !
                    
                      
                  time = NA,

                    		
                  

                  

                    266
                    !
                    
                      
                  variable = "lcl",

                    		
                  

                  

                    267
                    !
                    
                      
                  value = lcl) 

                    		
                  

                  

                    268
                    !
                    
                      
      rc.ucl <- rc.summ %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    269
                    !
                    
                      
        dplyr::transmute(ARM = "",

                    		
                  

                  

                    270
                    !
                    
                      
                  time = NA,

                    		
                  

                  

                    271
                    !
                    
                      
                  variable = "ucl",

                    		
                  

                  

                    272
                    !
                    
                      
                  value = ucl)

                    		
                  

                  

                    273
                    !
                    
                      
      rc <- rc %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    274
                    !
                    
                      
        dplyr::bind_rows(rc.lcl, rc.ucl)

                    		
                  

                  

                    275
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    276
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    277
                    
                    
                      
    # se requested

                    		
                  

                  

                    278
                    !
                    
                      
    if(se){

                    		
                  

                  

                    279
                    !
                    
                      
      rc.se <- rc.summ %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    280
                    !
                    
                      
        dplyr::transmute(ARM = "",

                    		
                  

                  

                    281
                    !
                    
                      
                  time = NA,

                    		
                  

                  

                    282
                    !
                    
                      
                  variable = "se",

                    		
                  

                  

                    283
                    !
                    
                      
                  value = se) 

                    		
                  

                  

                    284
                    !
                    
                      
      rc <- rc %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    285
                    !
                    
                      
        dplyr::bind_rows(rc.se)

                    		
                  

                  

                    286
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    287
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    288
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    289
                    !
                    
                      
    if("ARM" %in% names(rc.summ)){

                    		
                  

                  

                    290
                    !
                    
                      
      rc <- rc %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    291
                    !
                    
                      
        dplyr::mutate(ARM = rep(as.character(rc.summ$ARM), times = 1+2*ci+se))

                    		
                  

                  

                    292
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    293
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    294
                    !
                    
                      
    if("time" %in% names(rc.summ)){

                    		
                  

                  

                    295
                    !
                    
                      
      rc <- rc %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    296
                    !
                    
                      
        dplyr::mutate(time = rep(rc.summ$time, times = 1+2*ci+se))

                    		
                  

                  

                    297
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    298
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    299
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    300
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    301
                    
                    
                      
  # fix the format

                    		
                  

                  

                    302
                    !
                    
                      
  rc <- rc_struct %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    303
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::bind_rows(rc) 

                    		
                  

                  

                    304
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    305
                    !
                    
                      
  rc$type <- type

                    		
                  

                  

                    306
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    307
                    !
                    
                      
  return(rc)
