# Get model summary from \code{\link{fit_models}} objects

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
# Manipulates \code{\link{fit_models}} objects to get a model summary of AIC and BIC and status of whether the model converged or produced an error or warning.

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
# For more details and examples see the package vignettes:

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
# \itemize{

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#   \item \code{vignette("Fitting_models_in_R", package = "flexsurvPlus")}

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#   \item \code{vignette("Fitting_models_in_R_bootstrap", package = "flexsurvPlus")}

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#   \item \code{vignette("Survival_analysis_theory", package = "flexsurvPlus")}

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#   }

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
# @param models Object from \code{\link{fit_models}}

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
# @return A data frame containing the \code{\link{AIC}}, \code{\link{BIC}}

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#   from flexsurv objects and a status column of whether the model converged or produced an error or warning.

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
# @seealso \code{\link{fit_models}} \code{\link{flexsurvreg}}

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
get_model_summary <- function(models) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
  # Filter on flexsurv models

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    !
                    
                      
  flexsurvreg.test <- sapply(models, function(x) class(x)=="flexsurvreg")

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    !
                    
                      
  models.flexsurv  <- models[flexsurvreg.test]

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
  #models that produced an error or warning

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    !
                    
                      
  models.nonconverge <- models[flexsurvreg.test==FALSE]

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
  #test inputs before proceeding

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    !
                    
                      
  input.class <- sapply(models.flexsurv, class)

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    !
                    
                      
  assertthat::assert_that(

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    !
                    
                      
    all(input.class == "flexsurvreg"),

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    !
                    
                      
    msg = "get_params expects a list of 'flexsurvreg' objects as input. At least one of your inputs is not a flexsurvreg object"

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
  # fix bindings check

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    !
                    
                      
  name <- value <- NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    !
                    
                      
  output <-   tibble::enframe(models.flexsurv) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::mutate(

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    !
                    
                      
      Dist = name,

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    !
                    
                      
      AIC = sapply(models.flexsurv, stats::AIC), #get AIC

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    !
                    
                      
      BIC = sapply(models.flexsurv, stats::BIC), #get BIC

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    !
                    
                      
      Status = "Converged"

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    
                    
                      
    ) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::select(-value, -name) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    !
                    
                      
    as.data.frame()

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    !
                    
                      
  if(length(models.nonconverge)>0){

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    !
                    
                      
    non_converged_output  <- data.frame(

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    !
                    
                      
      Dist = names(models.nonconverge),

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    !
                    
                      
      AIC = NA,

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    !
                    
                      
      BIC = NA,

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    !
                    
                      
      Status = unlist(models.nonconverge))

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    !
                    
                      
    rownames(non_converged_output) <- c()

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    !
                    
                      
    output <- rbind(output, non_converged_output)

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    !
                    
                      
  output

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                
              

            

            

              

                
                  

                    1
                    
                    
                      
#' Extract information about non-parametric survival models

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' @param data A data frame containing individual patient data for the relevant

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#'   time to event outcomes.  

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' @param time_var Name of time variable in 'data'. Variable must be numerical and >0.

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' @param event_var Name of event variable in 'data'. Variable must be

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#'   numerical and contain 1's to indicate an event and 0 to indicate a censor.

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' @param weight_var Optional name of a variable in "data" containing case weights.

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' @param strata_var Name of stratification variable in "data". This is usually

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#'   the treatment variable and must be categorical. Not required if only one 

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#'   arm is being analyzed.

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' @param int_name Character to indicate the name of the treatment of interest,

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#'   must be a level of the "strata_var" column in "data", used for labelling

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#'   the parameters.

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#' @param ref_name Character to indicate the name of the reference treatment,

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#'    must be a level of the "strata_var" column in "data", used for labelling

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#'    the parameters. Not required if only one arm is being analyzed.

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#' @param types A list of statistics to extract - options include "survival", 

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#'    "cumhaz", "median", and "rmst". For details see the vignette on descriptive

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#'     analysis.

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#' @param t The time points to be used - this only controls the rmst statistic.

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#' @param ci Should a confidence interval be returned (TRUE or FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#' @param se Should a standard error be returned (TRUE or FALSE)

#' @param ... Additional arguments passed to \code{\link{survfit}}

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#' 

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
#' @return A data frame containing the following values and similar to that returned by \code{\link{summaryPSM}}

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
#' \itemize{

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item Model - returned as "Kaplan Meier"

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item ModelF - an ordered factor of Model

                    36

                    37
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item type - as defined by the types parameter.

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item variable - "est", "lcl", "ucl", "se" respectively

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item time - either NA or the time the statistic is evaluated at

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item value - estimated value

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    
                    
                      
#'   }

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    
                    
                      
#'   

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      
#'

#' require(dplyr)

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
#' require(ggplot2)

#' 

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      
#' PFS_data <- sim_adtte(seed = 2020, rho = 0.6) %>%

summaryKM <- function(data,

                    		
                  

                  

                    112
                    
                    
                      
                      time_var, event_var, weight_var = "",

    !missing(data),

    for (this.t in t){

        dplyr::group_by(ARM) %>%

                    !

                    !

                    !

                    !

                    !

                    405

                    407

        dplyr::group_by(ARM) %>%

                    !
                    
                      
        dplyr::mutate(lag_time = dplyr::lag(time),

                    		
                  

                  

                    409
                    !
                    
                      
                      lag_surv = dplyr::lag(survival),

                    		
                  

                  

                    410
                    !
                    
                      
          diff = time - lag_time,

          area = ifelse(time == 0, 0, diff*lag_surv)) %>%

                    413
                    !
                    
                      
          cum_area = sum(area),

        dplyr::transmute(

                    		
                  

                  

                    421
                    !
                    
                      
          ARM,

                    		
                  

                  

                    422

          type = "rmst",

          variable = "est",

                    		
                  

                  

                    424
                    !
                    
                      
          time = this.t,

                    		
                  

                  

                    425
                    !
                    
                      
          value = cum_area) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    426
                    !
                    
                      
        dplyr::bind_rows(rc)

                    		
                  

                  

                    427
                    
                    
                      
        

                    		
                  

                  

                    428
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    !
                    
                      
                    "Common shape", "Independent shape",

                    470

                    472
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    473
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                
              

            

            

              

                
                  

                    1
                    
                    
                      
#' Run a complete parametric survival analysis 

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' This function is a wrapper for the \code{\link{runPSM}} function intended to be run with the \code{\link{boot}} package. 

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' It enables running a complete parametric survival analysis for use when performing bootstrapping to explore uncertainty.

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' By re-using random seeds for each bootstrap sample it is possible to maintain correlations across multiple endpoints.

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' For more details and examples see the package vignettes:

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' \itemize{

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item \code{vignette("Fitting_models_in_R", package = "flexsurvPlus")}

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item \code{vignette("Bootstrap_models_in_R", package = "flexsurvPlus")}

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item \code{vignette("Model_theory", package = "flexsurvPlus")}

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#'   }

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' @param data A data frame containing individual patient data for the relevant

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#'   time to event outcomes. This is passed to the \code{data} argument of the

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#'   \code{\link{runPSM}} function

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#' @param i Index used to select a sample within \code{\link{boot}}.

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#' @param ... Additional parameters as used by \code{\link{runPSM}}

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#' @details  This function is intended to be used in conjunction with the

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#'   \code{\link{boot}} function to return the statistic to be

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#'   bootstrapped. In this case by performing parametric survival modelling using

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#'   {\link{flexsurv}} and returning the parameters of the survival distributions.

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#'    This is used as the 'statistic' argument in the boot function.

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#' @return The 'parameters_vector' object from the \code{\link{runPSM}} function.

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#'    'parameters_vector' is a vector which contains the coefficients for all of the flexsurv models specified.

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
#'    The column names are in the format 'modeltype.distribution.parameter.TreatmentName', for example, comshp.weibull.shape.Int refers to the shape parameter

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
#'     of the common shape weibull distribution for the intervention treatment and 'indshp.gengamma.mu.ref' refers to the mu parameter

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
#'     of the independent shape generalised gamma distribution for the reference treatment. Columns with 'TE' at the end are the treatment effect coefficients

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
#'      (applicable to the scale and shape parameters for independent shape models, applicable to the scale parameter only for the common shape

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
#'      model and not applicable for the separate model).

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
bootPSM <- function(data,

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
                    i,

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      
                   ...){

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    !
                    
                      
  data_boot <- data[i,]

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
  # call run_PSM (this does validity checks on inputs so no need to duplicate checks here)

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    !
                    
                      
  tryCatch({

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    !
                    
                      
    output <- runPSM(data = data_boot, ...)

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    !
                    
                      
    return(output$parameters_vector)

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
  })

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                  

                    45

# Fit flexsurv models

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
# Fits single or multiple \code{\link{flexsurv}} models using \code{\link{flexsurvreg}}.

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
# @param model.formula A survival model formula in the general form shown

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#   below. Note that variable names must match the corresponding columns in the

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#   data. This is passed to the \code{formula} argument of the

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#   \code{\link{fit_models}} function

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#  \itemize{

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#   \item Surv(Time, Event==1) ~ ARM is a model with a single covariate for the

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#   effect of treatment

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#   \item Surv(Time, Event==1) ~ 1 is a model with no covariates typically

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#   fitted to data from a single treatment group

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
# @param data A data frame containing individual patient data for the relevant

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#   time to event outcomes. This is passed to the \code{data} argument of the

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#   \code{\link{fit_models}} function

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
# @param distr A vector string of distributions, see dist argument in

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#   \code{\link{flexsurvreg}}. This is passed to the \code{distr} argument of

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#   the \code{\link{fit_models}} function

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
# @details Possible distributions include:

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
# \itemize{

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#   \item Exponential ('exp')

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#   \item Weibull ('weibull')

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#   \item Gompertz ('gompertz')

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
#   \item Log-normal ('lnorm')

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
#   \item Log-logistic ('llogis')

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
#   \item Generalized gamma ('gengamma')

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
#   \item Gamma ('gamma')

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
#   \item Generalised F ('genf')

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
#   }

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
# For more details and examples see the package vignettes:

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
# \itemize{

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
#   \item \code{vignette("Fitting_models_in_R", package = "flexsurvPlus")}

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      
#   \item \code{vignette("Fitting_models_in_R_bootstrap", package = "flexsurvPlus")}

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
#   \item \code{vignette("Survival_analysis_theory", package = "flexsurvPlus")}

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
#   }

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
#

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    
                    
                      
# @return A list containing flexsurv objects.

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    
                    
                      
# @seealso \code{\link{flexsurvreg}}

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
#

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      
# @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    
                    
                      
fit_models <- function(model.formula,

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
                       distr = c('exp',

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    
                    
                      
                                 'weibull',

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      
                                 'gompertz',

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    
                    
                      
                                 'lnorm',

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    
                    
                      
                                 'llogis',

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    
                    
                      
                                 'gengamma',

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    
                    
                      
                                 'gamma',

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    
                    
                      
                                 'genf'),

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    
                    
                      
                       data) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    
                    
                      
  #list of flexsurv objects

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    !
                    
                      
  output <-

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    !
                    
                      
    lapply(distr, fit_model, model.formula = model.formula, data = data)

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    !
                    
                      
  names(output) <- distr

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    !
                    
                      
  output

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    
                    
                      
}

# as data is produced by the internal functions can make assumptions on content and variable names

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    
                    
                      
# so if a variable named Weight is present we use it

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    
                    
                      
fit_model <- function(dist, model.formula, data) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    
                    
                      
  # fix for bindings check

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    !
                    
                      
  Weight <- NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    !
                    
                      
  model <-

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    !
                    
                      
    tryCatch({

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    !
                    
                      
      if ("Weight" %in% names(data)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    !
                    
                      
        flexsurv::flexsurvreg(

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    !
                    
                      
          formula = model.formula,

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    !
                    
                      
          data = data,

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    !
                    
                      
          dist = dist,

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    !
                    
                      
          weights = Weight

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    
                    
                      
        )

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    
                    
                      
      } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    !
                    
                      
        flexsurv::flexsurvreg(formula = model.formula,

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    !
                    
                      
                              data = data,

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    !
                    
                      
                              dist = dist)

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    
                    
                      
        

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    
                    
                      
    },

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    !
                    
                      
    error = function(e) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    !
                    
                      
      message("An error occurred in ", dist, ":\n", e)

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    !
                    
                      
      return("error")

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    
                    
                      
    },

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    !
                    
                      
    warning = function(w) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    !
                    
                      
      message("A warning occured in ", dist, ":\n",  w)

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    !
                    
                      
      return("warning")

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    
                    
                      
    },

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    !
                    
                      
    finally = {

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    !
                    
                      
      message("Fitting model ", dist)

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    
                    
                      
    })

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    
                    
                      
}

#' Convert survival parameters to SAS/STEM parametric forms

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' @param x An object created by calling \code{\link{runPSM}}

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' @param samples An object created by calling \code{\link{boot}} with \code{\link{bootPSM}}

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' @param use an optional character string giving a method for computing covariances in the presence of missing values. See  \code{\link{cov}} 

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#'            for details. Option "complete.obs" maybe needed when some bootstrap samples do not converge to estimate covariance only using

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#'            those that do. 

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' This function primarily exists for backward compatibility with older excel models where parametric extrapolation was

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' performed with SAS and alternative parametric forms were used for distributions. As such only a subset of models are supported.

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' One or both of \code{x} and \code{samples} must be specified and affect what is returned. For more details please see the 

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#' vignette \code{vignette("STEM_compatability", package = "flexsurvPlus")}

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' 

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' Possible distributions include

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#' 

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#' \itemize{

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item Exponential ('exp')

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item Weibull ('weibull')

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item Gompertz ('gompertz')

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item Log-normal ('lnorm')

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item Log-logistic ('llogis')

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item Generalized gamma ('gengamma')

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item Gamma ('gamma')

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#'   }

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#' @return a list containing 4 data frames

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#' \itemize{

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item stem_param Converted parameter estimates

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item stem_cov Converted covariance matrix (if \code{samples} provided)

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item stem_modsum Converted model summary (if \code{x} provided)

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item stem_boot Converted bootstrap samples (if \code{samples} provided)

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
#'   }

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
convSTEM <- function(x = NULL, samples = NULL, use = "everything"){

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
  #check that at least one object is provided

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    !
                    
                      
  assertthat::assert_that(

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    !
                    
                      
    !is.null(x) | !is.null(samples),

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    !
                    
                      
    msg = "One of x or samples must be provided"

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    
                    
                      
  # check x is an object from runPSM

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    !
                    
                      
  assertthat::assert_that(

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    !
                    
                      
    is.null(x) | any(names(x) == c("parameters_vector")),

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    !
                    
                      
    msg = "x must be created using runPSM"

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      
  # check samples is a bootstrap object

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    !
                    
                      
  assertthat::assert_that(

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    !
                    
                      
    is.null(samples) | class(samples) == "boot",

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    !
                    
                      
    msg = "samples must be a boot object"

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    !
                    
                      
  if (!is.null(samples)){

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    !
                    
                      
    assertthat::assert_that(

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    !
                    
                      
      all(unlist(lapply(strsplit(names(samples$t0), ".", fixed = TRUE), function(x){x[1]})) %in% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    !
                    
                      
            c("comshp", "indshp", "sep", "onearm")), 

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    !
                    
                      
      msg = "This function only works with bootstrap samples created using boot with statistic = bootPSM"

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    
                    
                      
  # check if both x and samples provided and are from same data/models

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    !
                    
                      
  if (!is.null(samples) & !is.null(x)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    !
                    
                      
    assertthat::assert_that(

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    !
                    
                      
      all(x$parameters_vector == samples$t0, na.rm = TRUE),

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    !
                    
                      
      msg = "x and samples provided do not match. Please confirm these are from the same models"

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    
                    
                      
  # fix no binding checks

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    !
                    
                      
  Estimate <- bootid <- BootSample <- Model <- Dist <- Param <- Value <- rowParam <- colParam <- NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    !
                    
                      
  ModelF <- DistF <- ParamF <- rowParamF <- colParamF <- NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    !
                    
                      
  AIC <- AIC_SAS <- BIC <- BIC_SAS <- Status <- NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    
                    
                      
  ####################################################################################

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    
                    
                      
  # conversion of the parameters to a data frame

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    
                    
                      
  ####################################################################################

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    
                    
                      
  # convert estimates to a data frame

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    
                    
                      
  # either from x or from samples t0

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    !
                    
                      
  if (!is.null(x)){

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    !
                    
                      
    ests <- cbind(Estimate = "Main", bootid = 0, as.data.frame(t(x$parameters_vector)))

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    
                    
                      
  } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    !
                    
                      
    ests <- cbind(Estimate = "Main", bootid = 0, as.data.frame(t(samples$t0)))

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    
                    
                      
  # if samples are provided then include these into the estimates dataframe

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    !
                    
                      
  if (!is.null(samples)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    !
                    
                      
    tsamp <- samples$t

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    !
                    
                      
    colnames(tsamp) <- names(samples$t0)

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
